1321	GSA Fundraising and Community Relations Committee	Mission of the FCR\r\nThe mission of the GSA Fundraising and Community Relations Committee (FCR) is to strategically plan and carry out fundraising initiatives and brand-building opportunities that strengthen the GSA and enhance its visibility within the University, alumni, and the broader community.\r\n\r\nLeadership of the FCR\r\nA. Chair and Vice-Chair\r\n\r\nThe FCR is chaired by the Executive Vice President (EVP).\r\n\r\nA Vice-Chair must be elected by the committee.\r\n\r\nB. Succession\r\n\r\nIf the EVP resigns, the GSA President will call the meeting, and the Vice-Chair will assume responsibility for chairing the committee to ensure continuity of business.\r\n\r\nFundraising Committee Policy\r\nThe FCR will follow all policies outlined in the FCR Handbook.\r\n\r\nAny changes to the FCR Handbook must be approved by a vote of the Fundraising Committee and confirmed by the GSA Senior Advisor.\r\n\r\nThe Handbook will include procedures for:\r\n\r\nCreating fundraising initiatives\r\n\r\nEstablishing timelines and strategies\r\n\r\nOutlining responsibilities and procedures\r\n\r\nFCR Strategy\r\nA. Initiative Design\r\nEach fundraising initiative must include:\r\n\r\nA clear fundraising purpose and target goals\r\n\r\nA strategic program plan\r\n\r\nAn action plan\r\n\r\nAn assessment plan\r\n\r\nB. Scope of Responsibility\r\n\r\nThe FCR’s responsibility is limited to fundraising. Once funds are raised for a specific purpose (e.g., scholarships or awards), the distribution of those funds is handled by the relevant committee (such as the Awards Committee).\r\n\r\nThe FCR may not determine how other committees allocate funds once fundraising goals are met.\r\n\r\nC. Collaboration\r\n\r\nThe GSA Council and other GSA Committees may submit fundraising requests to FCR to support growth and collaboration.\r\n\r\nCouncil Members may also request fundraising support on behalf of their colleges.\r\n\r\nD. Annual Planning\r\nAt the start of each academic year, the FCR will organize and develop strategies for both brand-building initiativesand fundraising initiatives.\r\n\r\nBrand-Building Initiatives\r\nThe FCR will develop strategies for at least two brand-building events per academic year, partnering with alumni, community, and/or industry leaders.\r\n\r\nPossible examples include the GSA Poster Symposium, Unity in Diversity, or the GSA Spring Awards.\r\n\r\nThe FCR must collaborate with the UNR Foundation Development Officers and, when necessary, other GSA Committees to plan these initiatives.\r\n\r\nFinal strategies must be discussed with the UNR Foundation Development Office before implementation.\r\n\r\nGSA Fundraising Initiatives\r\nThe FCR will develop strategies, as outlined in the FCR Handbook, for at least two fundraising initiatives per academic year.\r\n\r\nExamples may include: merchandise campaigns, food truck fundraisers, or a silent auction.\r\n\r\nAll fundraising strategies must be presented to and approved by the GSA Council.\r\n\r\nElection of FCR Members\r\nDuring the first meeting of the new GSA Council each academic year, the Council will elect four (4) representatives, including one (1) alternate, to serve on the FCR.	2026-04-28 02:29:42.16815-07	Active	{student_gov,community_svc}
