1322	GSA Judical, Budget and Finance Committee 	Mission of the JB&F\r\nThe mission of the Judicial, Budget, and Finance Committee (JB&F) is to:\r\n\r\nReview and amend the GSA Constitution and Bylaws as needed.\r\n\r\nReview and evaluate GSA policies to ensure compliance, clarity, and effectiveness.\r\n\r\nLeadership of the JB&F\r\nA. Chair and Vice-Chair\r\n\r\nThe JB&F is chaired by the Internal Vice President (IVP).\r\n\r\nA Vice-Chair must be elected by the committee.\r\n\r\nB. Succession\r\n\r\nIf the IVP resigns, the GSA President will call a JB&F meeting.\r\n\r\nThe Vice-Chair will assume responsibility for chairing the committee until further leadership is established.\r\n\r\nCensure, Grievances, and Removal Procedures\r\nThe JB&F will oversee all grievance and removal procedures as outlined in Article III of the GSA Bylaws.\r\n\r\nGSA Budget Process & Approval\r\nA. Budget Creation\r\n\r\nThe JB&F determines the annual GSA budget at the start of the academic year.\r\n\r\nOnce final enrollment numbers are published, the JB&F prepares a proposed budget and works with the GSA Senior Advisor and Executive Council to finalize it.\r\n\r\nThe proposed budget is presented to the GSA Council for approval at the first Council meeting of the academic year.\r\n\r\nB. Budget Approval Process\r\n\r\nThe Council may approve, amend, or reject the proposed budget.\r\n\r\nIf rejected, the budget is returned to the JB&F for revision.\r\n\r\nIf rejected twice, the GSA Executive Team, with the Senior Advisor present, will prepare a new budget proposal using the previous Fall’s approved budget as an interim budget.\r\n\r\nThe process repeats until the Council approves a budget.\r\n\r\nC. Reporting and Oversight\r\n\r\nAt the first Council meeting, the Senior Advisor must present the previous year’s financial report and the proposed budget for the new year.\r\n\r\nFinancial reports will also be provided upon request by the Executive Council or Council.\r\n\r\nD. Funding Restrictions\r\n\r\nRetroactive funding is prohibited.\r\n\r\nReimbursements of up to $50 may be approved by the Council for GSA Representatives, Executive Officers, or employees for expenses directly tied to GSA activities.\r\n\r\nReimbursement requests must be submitted within 30 days of purchase.\r\n\r\nThis rule may be waived if the Senior Advisor verifies that proper funding request procedures were followed.\r\n\r\nIndividual students may not be funded for academic pursuits outside of official GSA programs.\r\n\r\nJB&F Liaison Positions\r\nA. Role of Liaisons\r\n\r\nJB&F members will serve as liaisons to other GSA Committees.\r\n\r\nLiaisons ensure committees follow:\r\n\r\nGSA Bylaws\r\n\r\nNevada Open Meeting Laws\r\n\r\nRobert’s Rules of Order\r\n\r\nLiaisons also ensure committees remain within their approved budgets.\r\n\r\nB. Conflict of Interest\r\n\r\nA JB&F member serving on a committee cannot act as the liaison to that committee.\r\n\r\nC. Reporting and Enforcement\r\n\r\nIf violations occur (e.g., failing to post agendas/minutes, not meeting quorum, walking quorums), the liaison must report them to JB&F.\r\n\r\nJB&F will notify the committee chair, IVP, and Senior Advisor in writing to begin an investigation.\r\n\r\nThe committee has five (5) business days to respond in writing with an explanation.\r\n\r\nJB&F may then:\r\n\r\nAllow remedial actions, or\r\n\r\nRecommend removal of the chair or committee member(s).\r\n\r\nD. Escalation\r\n\r\nIf a second violation occurs, JB&F may escalate by requiring further evidence, beginning removal procedures, or recommending disciplinary action.\r\n\r\nRemoval of a Committee Chair requires:\r\n\r\nA two-thirds (⅔) vote of JB&F, and\r\n\r\nApproval from the Senior Advisor.\r\n\r\nJB&F may also recommend that the IVP remove a committee member.\r\n\r\nIn cases of substantive violations, JB&F may begin removal procedures as defined in Article III of the Bylaws.\r\n\r\nElection of JB&F Members\r\nAt the first meeting of the new GSA Council, the Council will elect four (4) representatives, including two (2) alternates, to serve on the JB&F.\r\n\r\nA Vice-Chair must be elected within the committee.\r\n\r\nThe Vice-Chair may lead meetings in the absence of the Chair.	2026-04-28 02:29:42.16815-07	Active	{student_gov}
